Intimate Concert on Historic Steamship
description: There is nothing else like this in Seattle or the world, that we know of! As this is not a typical music venue, our acoustic concert aboard a the Virginia V Steamship is incredibly unique. We also offer a very intimate listening environment that most traditional venues lack. This gives the musician an opportunity to connect with the audience and for the concert goers a very personal and meaningful experience.

itemListElement.name: Space Needle & Seattle Center Small Group Private Walking Tour

name: Space Needle & Seattle Center Small Group Private Walking Tour
description:
This Seattle tour has it all: art, history, culture, and incredible views from the top of the iconic Space Needle!

Our Seattle tour starts with a walk around the Queen Anne neighborhood and Seattle Center. As we pass by landmarks like the Museum of Pop Culture and Chihuly Garden and Glass, your local tour guide will point out the grounds lesser-known artworks and institutions, from the famous musical International Fountain to surrounding entertainment complexes like the Seattle Opera.

For any Seattle music fans, we can include a stop at a local radio station and record store to browse some vinyls and enjoy some local coffee. 

Then its off to the Space Needle for timed entry to the observation deck. Once there, youll enjoy a 360-degree Space Needle tour with your guide, who will point out other city landmarks and provide some Seattle history background.

After the tour, continue enjoying spectacular views of the city, Puget Sound, and on clear days, the Olympics and Mount Rainier!

review.name: Fantastic Tour of Seattle and the Space Needle.
review.reviewBody:
We had an absolutely brilliant time on this tour of Seattle and the iconic Space Needle! Our guide, Sam, was exceptional. His depth of knowledge about Seattles history and the stories of how the city was settled and built were both fascinating and engaging.

Sams storytelling was not only insightful but also sprinkled with humor, which made the tour even more enjoyable. He had a great way of bringing history to life and connecting it to the vibrant city Seattle is today.

The Space Needle itself was, of course, a highlight, but it was Sams guidance throughout the day that truly made the experience memorable. I would highly recommend this tour to anyone visiting Seattlewhether its your first time or youre a local looking to rediscover the city!

review.name: Book THIS tour
review.reviewBody: Wonderful tour and very worth it! Our tour guide William was so knowledgeable and affectionate about this beautiful city and its history- the space needle tour does not disappoint and neither does walking around and learning about the meaning and symbolism behind your surroundings.

review.name: Great custom tour
review.reviewBody: William was patient, knowledgeable, and worked with our group's special needs. We enjoyed a custom tour that included the Space Needle, IMAX, movie, walking tour, and the Armory. I appreciated his unique perspective, although it was hard to hear him occasionally as he is soft spoken.

review.name: Seattle walking tour
review.reviewBody: He is very knowledgeable about the  history of Seattle, and he didn't make the tour feel like it was too long, I appreciated his  restaurant recommendations at Pike's Place Market as well.

review.name: City and Space Needle Tour
review.reviewBody: Great tour.  William was incredibly knowledgeable and courteous.   Highly reccomend him.   Tour of the city and Space Needle.

review.name: Excellent tour
review.reviewBody: William was an excellent guide and so willingly shared so much great information about his home city. We totally enjoyed the tour.

review.name: Trip to Seattle
review.reviewBody: The review was amazing. Everywhere we stopped William went into great detail about the art and every place we stopped. He was a great tour guide and would strongly recommend him to anybody visiting Seattle.

review.name: SPACE NEEDLE
review.reviewBody: Amazing view, and very informative guide! Gave very informative details of not only the needle and the fair grounds, but of the area around it too.

review.name: Sehr gut

review.name: Top Tour

itemListElement.name: Seattle Half Day Tour with Space Needle, Boat Ride & Underground

name: Seattle Half Day Tour with Space Needle, Boat Ride & Underground
description:
Welcome aboard the Best of Seattle experience with Tripshepherd. 

Our exploration starts with the futuristic Space Needle. Bask in the panoramic cityscape views from this architectural marvel.

Next, we embark on a scenic city drive, a brief immersion into the city's lively pulse. The journey continues with a serene harbor cruise, a unique opportunity to appreciate Seattle's waterfront.

Our adventure then takes an intriguing turn underground with the renowned Beneath the Streets experience. As we navigate forgotten paths and alleys, you'll discover the underground areaways born out of Seattle's resilient rebirth, providing a unique glimpse into the city's vibrant past.

As we traverse the city, we'll cruise by renowned landmarks like the historic Smith Tower, the eclectic Seattle Art Museum, and the bustling Pike Place Market.

The journey concludes at Kerry Park, where stunning views of the city skyline, the majestic Mount Rainier, and the shimmering waters of Elliott Bay await.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Enchanting Night Tour with Space Needle and Skywheel

name: Seattle Enchanting Night Tour with Space Needle and Skywheel
description:
Join us on a thrilling night experience in the amazing city of Seattle, where we invite you to discover the hidden gems of the Emerald City. 

Our first stop is the iconic Great Wheel, known as the tallest wheel in the western United States. Step into one of the spacious cabins and ascend high above the city, taking in the panoramic vistas that will leave you awe-inspired. 

Next, we venture to the picturesque Kerry Park, renowned for its stunning views. 

Following our time at Kerry Park, we embark on a leisurely drive to the acclaimed Space Needle. Marvel at the striking architecture of this symbol of innovation as we arrive at its doorstep. Ascend to the observation deck and be greeted by a breathtaking 360-degree panorama of the cityscape. 

We continue our adventure with a captivating city drive, where you'll witness the energetic pulse of Seattle. 

Join Tripshepherd for this great night experience.

I called several times with them constantly hanging up. I called the 800 number and finally got ahold of someone after 2 days to send in a confirmation to get your guide so I can get a refund. Very bad business. I felt scammed.

itemListElement.name: 3 Hours Electric Bike Tour of Seattle's Waterways, Nature and Neighborhoods

name: 3 Hours Electric Bike Tour of Seattle's Waterways, Nature and Neighborhoods
description: The electric bikes make taking a three hour tour effortlessly. You will ease up the hills of Seattle while smiling. After the tour you will have seen many unique sites, expanded your knowledge of the waterways, the animals of the Sound and the neighborhoods, and you will have had an enjoyable and memorable experience that's truly all about Seattle. The electric bikes allow for close up viewing of the gardens, boat docks and other sites. Your guide is a local. I grew up in Seattle, taught in Seattle schools, I care about the city and the natural settings and continue to build my knowledge of Seattle. The helmets have an intercom system that helps us communicate while riding the bikes. Your safety is a priority, we stick mainly to bike paths and lightly traveled roads. Please check out the reviews on my website. Must be 16 to take the tour. The bikes are only designed for adults. I charge per bike. I do not charge for children riding on the back of the cargo bike.

review.name: Unique way to see Seattle
review.reviewBody: Awesome way to explore the city. Went with friends who had previously lived in Seattle for a couple years and they saw parts of the city they'd never seen before and really enjoyed it. Highly recommend.

review.name: Best Bike Tour in Seattle!  MUST DO!!!
review.reviewBody: We were gifted this when we first moved to Seattle and then we purchased two additional rides for friends!  I have to say... this is an INCREDIBLE experience.  Joe was our tour guide and we could not have asked for a better tour guide.  Joe is incredibly kind, so knowledgable and it is clear he is passionate about the history of Seattle and delighted his guests.  He took us some epic spots we have never visited even after living here for 3 years!  You even get to play a game at the end of the ride and the prize for the winner is pretty epic too! :) Joe....  we will keep telling everyone we know who comes to visit to do this amazing experience! Thank you for a wonderful day out exploring this beautiful city!

review.name: Worthwhile tour
review.reviewBody: Overall the tour was well done and worthwhile. It is a great way to see other neighborhoods in Seattle and David has great historical and fun information on the city. You see the Seattle Locks, views, salmon, troll under the bridge , etc. The tour starts in front of an apartment home in the Ballard neighborhood. David was our guide and he is the owner as well.

review.name: Scenery tour of the waterway in Ballard Seattle.
review.reviewBody: Our guide David was very informative and courteous.   It was our first experience on an electric bike.    David navigated the tour on the best roads and scenery.   Would highly recommend.

review.name: Best tour of Seattle!!!
review.reviewBody: Really great experience. I loved the sights and views. Dave was especially informative and the prize at the end was well worth the bingo game.  I have done 3 electric bike tours in my travels around the world and granted the last two weren't with native English speakers, but this by far was the best. I would absolutely recommend this tour for those who don't know the city and for those that do and don't get out much to see the great history of seattle.  They provide everything you need and they even do a wonderful job of explaining how to ride electric bikes for those who have not ridden one. Im a beginner mountain biker and sometimes see electric bikes as "cheating", but i feel like electric bikes are the best way to explore the city and allow yourself to take in the sights and views without being worn out. I would definitely do this tour again because there is so much to see and remember. They are patient, helpful, safe,  and most of all very kind. This tour is excellent for all age groups and people from all walks of life.

review.name: Joe the great
review.reviewBody: Joe was an amazing tour guide and overall good guy. Extremely helpful with the bikes and knows everything there is to know about the city and surrounding area. He was laid back about the time spent on the tour and extremely accommodating. You couldnt ask for a better tour guide and company to take you around Seattle, take this tour!!

review.name: Wonderful Tour!
review.reviewBody: Whenever we travel one of our go to's to doing a bike tour, we just find it's a wonderful to get acclimated to the area. Joe and David did a fantastic job in doing just this, they couldn't have been more engaging and knowledgeble about the area. The e-bikes were a blast and they were extremely careful making sure everyone was comfortable. I would highly recommend this tour as a must do when visiting Seattle.

review.name: Top notch e bike tour
review.reviewBody: A fantastic e-bike experience. The perfect balance of information and activity. We absolutely loved the view from Gasworks park. Just one of many highlights from Joe and David. We would highly recommend this tour!!

review.name: Best way to see Seattle
review.reviewBody:
Awesome experience on the bikes exploring Seattle. Our guides Joe & David were the best !

They both knew lots of history about the city. This is our 3rd time in Seattle and one of our favorite tours! 

Plus the weather could not have been nicer! 

Thanks for an awesome day!

review.name: Superb introduction to Neighbors neighborhoods outside of downtown Seattle
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour of Seattle neighborhoods, canal front, to include Canal lock system, and fish ladder. Tour guide was personable and knowledgeable. This tour requires a modicum of agility and balance to manage frequent stop and gos on heavy e-bikes which made easy work of Seattles hilly terrain.

name: Drag Queen Food Tour
description:
Take a seat, Honey. Seattle's most stunningly glamorous guides await you on this 2.5 hour walking food tour through Pike Place Market... and beyond. 

Your admission includes 10 generously portioned food tastings from Downtown Seattle's most beloved and LGBTQ+ friendly businesses - But we know that's not why you're here. 

You're here for the GLAM. 

You'll find yourself immersed amongst the madness of our city's historic market. Let your Queen lead you and discover something new. 

Seattle is a place to come to discover the best versions of your favorite foods. If you have preferences and/or allergies please let us know ahead of time so we can do something Extra Special for you. 

Seattle is also home to a culture of people who know what's worth fighting for. It's the reason why we can lead these tours in a historic farmers market, and it is the reason why our guides are free to be colorful in a city famous for gray skies. 

I hope you'll join us!

Your Queen has Arrived!!

name: Uncovering Seattle's Hidden Gems
description:
Seattles architecture and art scene is second to none. On this walking tour, youll get to see incredible works and get to know beautiful Uptown Seattle.

Well board the monorail for a quick ride to Seattle Center, home of the towering Space Needle, the mind-bending Museum of Pop Culture, and creative works meant to inspire, invite, and invoke the nature of the Pacific Northwest. Your guide will let you know how to arrange admission to any of the areas venues for after your tour.

Throughout the Center, well explore a nearby local radio studio, pass by a sustainable sports arena, and get a chance to stop in at some of the neighborhoods best coffee shops and bakeries.

With your pastry and beverage in hand, youll be ready to trek your way uphill to enjoy fabulous city skyline views or head out of the neighborhood to relax along the beautiful Puget Sound waterfront. Your guide will have plenty of recommendations for where to eat, drink, and sightsee in Seattle!

review.name: Excellent art and architecture focused tour
review.reviewBody: Kieth was super friendly, very knowledgeable and clearly passionate about the history of Seattle. My husband and I ended up being the only two in the tour, however that didnt impact our experience. We would highly recommend this tour!

review.name: Great experience that highlights the parts of Seattle Center that you normally wouldn't pay attention to.
review.reviewBody: Keith was really knowledgeable and an overall fun and friendly guide. He helped highlight many parts of downtown that you'd ordinarily just walk by, and his explanations helped add another dimension of connection to the city. Now when we walk by some of these public works, we'll be more appreciative of them because of the stories they tell.

review.name: Informative and enjoyable experience with a great guide
review.reviewBody: Really enjoyed this tour with a personable, knowledge and enthusiastic tour guide (Keith). I learnt a lot about the history of the architecture in Seattle, and really enjoyed visiting the public art around the Seattle centre, which it was really great to hear Keiths thoughts on, as well as lots of interesting facts about the various pieces.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Pike Place Market Food Tour

name: Seattle Pike Place Market Food Tour
description:
Experience Seattles iconic Pike Place Market in the most unique way possible, by letting our local guides delight you with a fusion of Pacific Northwest staples and immigrant-inspired cuisine.

On this tour, youll get to know the history behind the market and the citizens who have helped preserve its character to this day. Youll get to meet the locals, perhaps spot some flying fish, and pass by two renown attractions: the notorious Gum Wall and the original Starbucks!

Youll also get to enjoy local eats from hearty fish stew to fresh local cheeses and fruits. Well combine these local foods with cuisine inspired by immigrants who have brought their own style, ingredients, and stories to Seattle over the past century and a half.

Maybe youll try a savory stuffed pastry, indulge in a cinnamon-coated cookie, or enjoy the perfect pairing of a locally roasted coffee and a decadent yogurt. While you eat, youll be even happier knowing youre supporting the market with your ticket price!

itemListElement.name: Preserving Pike Place: Market Community Tour

name: Preserving Pike Place: Market Community Tour
description:
Get a truly unique perspective of Seattles iconic Pike Place Market on this walking tour that gives back to the marketplace community! Your local guide will lead you through the maze of the market, exploring its evolution through the historic buildings and stories of vendors past and present.

Along the way, we may catch a show of the famous flying fish, pass the oldest existing Starbucks, and make our way to one of the citys most unusual attractions, the Gum Wall. 

While youll get to experience the most visited sites of the market, youll also receive a deep appreciation of the Pike Place Market Foundation and the array of services they provide to create a strong community that keeps the market going and benefits those in need.

Best yet, your ticket price already includes a donation to the Foundation, so youll be giving back to the community yourself!

Your guide will point out great places to eat, drink, and explore based on your interests for the rest of your stay in Seattle!

review.name: Informative and fun tour
review.reviewBody: Fantastic tour, full of information about Pike Place Market... Highly recommend.  Great overview of what's there. History and interesting. Becky was fantastic.

review.name: Party of One
review.reviewBody: Due to a clerical error, I was the only one on the tour that day. It was great! Lee, the tour guide, took me all around and gave me an in-depth tour. He even waited while I ordered food. I appreciated the commitment to the tour, even with just one person. Definitely will take another tour they offer.

name: Sugo Hand Roll Bar
description: Sugo is Seattle's first dedicated Hand Roll Bar. Our menu highlights sustainable seafood and pairs wonderfully with our selection of unique cocktails. Make a reservation fpr your seats at the hand roll bar or in the Sugo dining room for our tabletop experience featuring nigiri omakase and more. 18+ after 5pm for the entire restaurant.

itemListElement.name: Mt. Rainier Tour and Guided Hike

name: Mt. Rainier Tour and Guided Hike
description:
This tour is unique in that you will be on guided shorter hikes in Mt. Rainier National Park. From November to June snowshoes/crampons will be provided when necessary since there is often snow on the trails in those months. 
We hike a few miles throughout the day and you will experience diverse landscapes and scenery such as glaciers, mountains, waterfalls, rivers, lakes, and tall trees in old-growth forest which are all the highlights in Mount Rainier National Park.
(In the winter areas of the park may be closed some days and not all highlights will be accessible at times).

review.name: Highly recommend
review.reviewBody: I had a great time on this tour with our guide Susan. She took us to the mountain to start hiking, had the poles and snow shoes for us to wear. Made sure everybody made it up safely. Had a picnic in a spot on the mountain where the view was breath taking. After we descended the mountain, took us to a few more spots in the park for great pictures and unforgettable experiences. I definitely recommend.

review.name: Majestic, up close and personal, friendly guide
review.reviewBody:
Epic day trip to Mt Rainier!  So glad we
Booked this excursion as we were able to experience the area up close and personal. Beautiful majestic sites throughout the day. Hike in/out was more strenuous than expected due to the snow. Susan was a great guide! Very knowledgeable about the area and patient with all requests.

review.name: Mt Rainer activists
review.reviewBody: Amazing experience hiking on the snow and forest of mt rainier. I would definitely recommend it. It is  an all day activity. 10/10

review.name: Dont miss this! If youre in good condition to hike.
review.reviewBody: This was amazing! I had no idea we would be hiking up Mt Rainier with deep snow. The shoe attachments were key but I was wearing sneakers so my feet got soaked. It was challenging because you would sink into the snow every so often . But so worth it. The views are spectacular and having lunch on a glacier is an incredible experience. We then hiked to a couple of waterfalls and a forest area so got to see all aspects of Mt Rainier. Susan was wonderful and very knowledgeable. Plenty of of bathroom facilities along the way so that was much appreciated.

review.name: First hiking experience
review.reviewBody: She made my first time hiking, the best and I learned a lot from her. She explained a lot about thr mountain and locations and was very generous the whole time.

review.name: Excellent tour, Susan!
review.reviewBody: Susan was an absolutely excellent tour guide! She gave us all the ins and outs of the plants, the trees the water. She included everything we could possibly want to know about Mount Rainier.

review.name: A couple of Aussies in the snow.
review.reviewBody: Nate was a great guide. Plenty of knowledge of the areas we visited and a very friendly chap. For us Aussies, this was an amazing experience to hike in fresh snow, picnic amongst the trees at the peak of our hike.. there were a few snow fights, snow angel's and plenty of stops for some great photography.. it really was one of the highlights of our holiday.

review.name: Most Amazing Experience Ever
review.reviewBody:
I cannot say enough about how incredible this day has been!  Nate, our guide, was the absolute best - kind, patient, informative, and fun. The weather was PERFECT, and the views were incredible.  God truly showed out. 10 out of 10 recommend this tour for this time of year.  

One note:  this tour is recommended for ages 8 - 85. I think ability definitely depends on the time of year.  This is a physically demanding tour when snow and ice are on the ground. I am a runner and would not recommend for anyone under 13 or over 65 (not in good physical health) during the snowy season.

Definitely an incredible tour, and Inwould definitely do again!

review.name: Amazing tour, amazing views!
review.reviewBody:
This trip was AMAZING! Our tour guide Susan was knowledgeable, friendly, and helpful. The pick up time and location was right on and the ride out to the mountain was very comfy. After we put our snowshoes on and got our poles, Susan led us up the mountain. I was a little worried as Id never snowshoed before but it went smoothly after getting the hang of it. 

The views all around were spectacular! I recommend dressing in layers because youll be cold at first but youll want to shed your jacket about 5 minutes into the climb. 

After reaching the base again, we went to see Narada Falls (beautiful) and stopped at a number of other equally beautiful nature scenes. If youre given the option of skipping anything, DONT! See everything you can! You wont regret it!

review.name: Beautiful Mt Rainier
review.reviewBody:
Simply spectacular.  The weather was perfect with clear blue skies making it perfect conditions for our trip.

Comfortable drive out to the park and pick up on time where designated.

We hiked a fair way up to a nice spot to have our picnic with all snow shoes and walking poles provided.  Various other stops after to see waterfalls, scenic spots, a running glacial river and an old growth forest.

My only suggestion would be the advert needs to be clearer regarding the strenuous nature of the snow hike and the suitability for some people.  We were probably the oldest in the group at mid 40s and fairly good fitness and we found it a little tough.

itemListElement.name: Guided forest hike to Seattle waterfalls incl. Snoqualmie Falls

name: Guided forest hike to Seattle waterfalls incl. Snoqualmie Falls
description: This tour is unique in that you hike (moderate level) in old-growth forest along Snoqualmie River for a few hours to view a gorgeous cascade of falls, Twin Falls followed by viewing another beautiful fall that we drive to - the famous 270-foot tall Snoqualmie Falls. You also see a beautiful lake with views of the surrounding mountains often reflected in the lake. There is lots of diversity on this half day tour from Seattle.

review.name: Great Day Out
review.reviewBody: Delightful hike and beautiful views. Guide was knowledgeable and made everyone feel comfortable and included. The guide drove safely to and from all the destinations and paced the day well.

review.name: love the trip
review.reviewBody: we had a great time on the tour.  the weather was great and we love the hike.  Our guide, Nate, was wonderful and very engaged with everyone.  Highly recommended.

review.name: Great half day tour of the falls!
review.reviewBody: Nate was a great tour guide - very knowledgeable and informative on the area. We took lots of amazing pictures of the falls! Would definitely recommend.

review.name: Great value and gorgeous hike
review.reviewBody: The weather was perfect. Nate, our guide was great at ensuring everyone was comfortable on the hike. The views of the falls were gorgeous. Would highly recommend this tour!

review.name: Guided forest hike to Seattle waterfalls incl. Snoqualmie Falls
review.reviewBody:
Amazing nature hike!!! Was worthed the weather was perfect for the hike
Nate is an amazing tour guide and friendly very caring person. We had a good time!!!

review.name: Astonishing hike
review.reviewBody: Susan was wonderful! So kind, friendly, and  knowledgeable. I would definitely take this tour again and recommend to friends! Susan really truly is the best!

review.name: Terrific twin falls!!
review.reviewBody: Fabulous hike to twin falls with Susan and our small group. Would definitely recommend this trip regardless of the time of year. The views were spectacular in February with the snow and ice on the ground. Us two newbies found walking with crampons super easy. Susan is a wonderful guide with lots of cool ecological information (and nice snacks!).

review.name: Multiple Mt Rainier stops
review.reviewBody: Wonderful experience and guide! Snowshoeing at paradise was paradise. Waterfalls and forest hike breathtaking. Moderate and above hiking.

review.name: A nice hike not far from Seattle.
review.reviewBody: We were passing through Seattle on a short trip, and wanted to see some sights outside of town. Beautiful scenery. Susan was a great guide and pointed out lots of interesting things to see and learn about. A fun hike that does include some areas of incline and stairs, but not too challenging. Take a backpack to shed or add clothing layers if needed. Bottled water was provided. Bathrooms at the trailhead. Would recommend this to anyone who doesnt want to commit to an all day event.

review.name: Great host and experience!
review.reviewBody: Excellent experience and host! We are so glad we took this opportunity to explore the area! I was attending a conference so the half-day trip was perfect. Highly recommend!
